  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Intraoperative floppy iris syndrome (IFIS) is a recently described condition observed during
      cataract surgery. It has been hypothesized that irreversible atrophy of the iris dilator
      muscle associated with α1-adrenergic receptor antagonists (α1-ARA) is responsible for IFIS.
      However the prevalence of IFIS in Korean population is not reported. The purpose of this
      study is to evaluate the prevalence and clinical manifestations of IFIS in relation to iris
      anatomical change in Korean patients taking α1-ARA.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
